  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial: coverage gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation results span the nominal operating envelope (2–5 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM); edge-case operating points named in the COU (sub-1 L/min low-flow states and maximum-speed 5000 RPM runaway conditions associated with high-shear-stress hemolysis) are addressed in companion work that is not linked to this package.",
